default3. ORR staffing:default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;default&#xa0;default&#xa0;default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;default&#xa0;
defaultWe devote significant resources to level crossings work. We undertake level crossing work through technical expertise and inspections and investigations across the country.   
default&#xa0;
defaultWe have 86 warrant holding health and safety inspectors who all have received extensive training in level crossings. We have a team of inspectors who are dedicated to level crossing work. 
default&#xa0;
defaultAll of our inspectors have level crossing expertise. Skills are developed through both our in house competency management training and external training through Birmingham University’s School of Railway Engineering Integration Programme which includes specific technical based training on level crossings. Our in house training consists of theory and practical experience of level crossings which involves a large practical element. Our inspectors also undertake other technical engineering training provided by industry experts. 
default&#xa0;
defaultAcross ORR, we have 26 engineers 
default(22 of whom are inspectors
default), and of these 7 have signalling engineering qualifications. 
defaultAll of our engineers have either IRSE and/or IET qualifications. (Institute of Engineering Technology, which is a broader qualification than IRSE.) 
defaultLevel crossing engineering expertise is not unique to one engineering discipline. It requires a multi discipline approach therefore we draw on experience from across the office to perform our safety functions. We also have access to other consulting 
defaultand expert 
defaultengineers to support our work. 
default&#xa0;
defaultBreakdown of ORR staffdefault&#xa0;
defaultBelow is a breakdown of the ORR complement of 289 staff for 2013-14 as set out in our Business Plan. This includes all posts (filled or vacant) and includes decimal places for part time employees.
